DEVELOPMENT FUNDS 

 
Subject to a successful Token Sale of HGT by HGF, it is envisaged that HGF will give grants to 
HelloGold to support the development of HelloGold in the following ways: 
 

1. Market expansion 
2. Product improvement and technical development 
3. Tech team expansion – required to implement 1. and 2. 

 
 
1. MARKET EXPANSION 
 
The key drivers of HelloGold AUM are number of customers and amount of gold held by each 
customer. The best way to increase the number of active customers is via expansion into new 
geographic markets. The grants received from HGF (if any) will determine which markets can be 
entered, and accelerate the entry into these markets. 
 
 

 

Market expansion will require spend in 4 key areas: 
 

1. In country teams – Set up and run in-
country operations, including local customer 
service and marketing (language driven) 

2. Tech team – Scale up the tech team to get 
in-house specialists and the ability to 
respond to the challenges of both 
development and operating in multiple 
countries. This will include creating versions 
of the app for different countries 
(internationalisation inc. language, country 
specific payment systems, changes caused 
by different regulatory environments, 
different cultures, partner requirements etc) 

3. Marketing – Due to the mass market nature 
of the product, country specific marketing 
(style, content, language) is critical to 
creating product acceptance and take up. 
Expanding into different countries will 
require additional headcount for digital 
marketing (inc social media management in 
local languages) 

4. Additional overhead, particularly working 
capital required for a larger gold float (gold 
available for sale) 

 
Note: HelloGold’s expansion has costs in base/local currency (not crypto) and therefore the ability to 
accelerate our expansion and grow AUM is determined by the base currency amount 
raised/equivalent when ETH is released. 
  



HelloGold Foundation Limited. 
