BUDGET 
 
HelloGold has produced an expected operating budget based on anticipated Year 1 and Year 3 
spend. 
 
HelloGold 3-Year Budget 
 

 
 
The change in percentage of each segment between Year 1 and Year 3 reflects the relative costs of 
expanding into new markets. 
 
Team covers employment (staff) costs. HelloGold will expand our tech team and set up operational 
and marketing staff in new markets. The team cost as a portion of total reduces over time, as 
HelloGold will be able to benefit from scale. 
Gold Capex is the working capital cost of buying and storing gold reserves. With increased scale, the 
gold reserves will make up a smaller portion of total costs compared to setting up operations in new 
markets. 
Marketing covers direct to market activities, supporting integration with business partners, and 
promotions. As HelloGold enters new, larger markets we will increase our marketing spend 
accordingly. 



HelloGold Foundation Limited. 
Private & Confidential.  

23

Office includes expenses used to run HelloGold offices and related administrative costs, more people 
in more locations leads to increased spend.  
Architecture refers to the cost of maintaining and improving tech systems, including mobile 
development and web services. 
Security Audit means third party auditing of HelloGold systems. 
Non-Gold Capex covers fixed assets including computer and mobile phone hardware. 
Other captures all other third party fees including legal services, Shariah advisory and licensing. 
Contingency is calculated as a percentage of the total budget. Over time, HelloGold will allocate 
more finances towards this fund (up to 10%) as the bigger expansion plan will have greater 
uncertainty and more “unknown unknowns” which may require funds. 
 
 
